Title: Walker, Texas Ranger: Season 6

reviewText: When you buy this, please remember that it is actually the Seventh Season according to many websites such as [...] (the reason for this is because the first season was actually seasons one and two). With that said, according to the episode list, we only have ONE more release left and the entire awesome show is out on dvd!!!!!Anyway, this season isn't any exception to the others. It stars Chuck Norris as a Texas Ranger, and his partner Trivette. They go out and solve crimes. There are some interesting episodes for this release. I love the second part of The Wedding which feature Walker pulverizing criminals because they hurt his chick Alex. So Walker interviews people by first unplugging the camera system, then plugging it back in only to feature a bloody mess singing like a canary. Other great episodes include livegirls.now which features some of the show's ridiculous, unrealistic view of real life crimes.This dvd season comes differently than the previous ones. If you bought the previous seasons, you got a box set, with each case listing episodes and one dvd. This season is just one standard size DVD box with dvds stacked together in a book like fashion and the episodes are listing on transparent tabs on each side of the case. This feels a bit rushed and it looks odd on the shelf with my other collections. So this is a big no-no in my opinion. Hopefully cbs won't go cheap on the next release.
summary: Only one more to go, I think!!!!!
Title: Walker, Texas Ranger: Season 6

Title: Walker, Texas Ranger: Season 6

reviewText: It seems like every season is better than the last. Now with only one remaining to be released (Season 7) I can't wait for that realise. Season 6 of Walker changed over to the multi-pack clam shell case which is being used by most of the CBS releases (Raw Hide, Untouchables, The Fugitive, Gomer Pyle U.S.M.C. among many others. This new packaging takes up half the space, which is good. The episodes are of the high quality we are used to from the prior releases. It is a must own, but considering Season 6 ends with a cliff hanger, let's hope season 7 is realised soon!
Title: Walker, Texas Ranger: Season 6

reviewText: This is one of my favorite seasons. This season has great episodes on it! One reason why I liked the season so much was because Walker and Alex got engaged on this one! It has 23 episodes on it. I have enjoyed all of the episodes. I have always been a fan of Walker Texas Ranger and I even recorded every episode on vhs tapes so that I can watch them over and over. I have since thrown those away because I wore them out and now I have this great series on dvd to watch over and over again! I have about all of the episodes memorized and still enjoy the series! If I had to make the choice whether to buy it again then I definitely would without a doubt! In fact I have all the seasons on dvd now I just wish they would release the episode Trial By Fire on dvd too! This is a must buy for all Walker Texas Ranger fans!!!
Title: Walker, Texas Ranger: Season 6
